they already have degrees,

00:24:10.370 --> 00:24:16.140
PhD statistics, MA chemistry,
and that disconnect is well

00:24:16.140 --> 00:24:22.940
in a wide range of our
society and complain

00:24:22.940 --> 00:24:28.510
that although they are
educated they are not happy.

00:24:28.510 --> 00:24:34.690 position:56%
Then you have what we did not expect
to find in snowballing samples,

00:24:34.690 --> 00:24:42.660 position:56%
which is that migration is framed as
an alternative to home conditions.

00:24:42.660 --> 00:24:45.810
But a large percentage says
that they made a mistake.

00:24:45.810 --> 00:24:48.670
We're not expecting to find that.

00:24:48.670 --> 00:24:51.710
We're expecting to say that they're
happy that they've left Ghana

00:24:51.710 --> 00:24:58.290
or Sierra Leone, but that's not
what we've been able to find.

00:24:58.290 --> 00:25:02.020
And we've been asking the
questions, why are they sad,

00:25:02.020 --> 00:25:08.170
why are they not very
happy with this issue?

00:25:08.170 --> 00:25:12.740
And there are so many answers,

00:25:12.740 --> 00:25:15.220
but two of which are
very important issues

00:25:15.220 --> 00:25:17.540 position:56%
around what I call cultural capital.

00:25:17.540 --> 00:25:20.200
What is it that you have
before you come here?

00:25:20.200 --> 00:25:23.220
And issues are on social prestige.

00:25:24.280 --> 00:25:28.320
Values of social prestige
are not universal.

00:25:28.320 --> 00:25:31.940
For instance, it was when I got
to the US that I washed a car

00:25:31.940 --> 00:25:33.760
for the first time in my life.

00:25:33.760 --> 00:25:37.640
A professor doesn't wash
cars where I come from.

00:25:37.640 --> 00:25:43.270
Nobody does that, because of
the higher social prestige

00:25:43.270 --> 00:25:44.830
of the professor.

00:25:44.830 --> 00:25:49.500
What you call a business card, I
can write a note at the back of it

00:25:49.500 --> 00:25:51.600
and it will give you a job.

00:25:51.600 --> 00:25:55.450
Not here. That's why I
don't carry one anymore

00:25:55.450 --> 00:25:59.500
because I quickly realize
that it's just an address.

00:25:59.500 --> 00:26:02.620
It's just to say I'm in Austin.

00:26:02.620 --> 00:26:05.860
It's not tied to issues
around prestige.

00:26:05.860 --> 00:26:12.580
And you find and later in Dallas
and Houston how they've been trying

00:26:12.580 --> 00:26:15.940
to recreate those notions
of social prestige.

00:26:15.940 --> 00:26:19.410
I once attended a party
as part of this research

00:26:19.410 --> 00:26:23.180
and with the celebrant came into
the hall with a white horse.

00:26:24.210 --> 00:26:32.630 position:56%
