some of what they do.

01:31:14.070 --> 01:31:21.270
But fundamentally, since the fall
of apartheid, we've been struggling

01:31:21.270 --> 01:31:25.350
to create one common-- one
reason, one common cause

01:31:25.350 --> 01:31:30.900
that will unite blacks on
both sides of the Atlantic.

01:31:30.900 --> 01:31:36.630
So, anti-colonial struggles,
domestic US politics

01:31:36.630 --> 01:31:38.750
and civil rights united them,

01:31:38.750 --> 01:31:41.790
anti-apartheid struggles
united them.

01:31:41.790 --> 01:31:46.770
But today, there has been
not a single one cause.

01:31:46.770 --> 01:31:54.780
And until we get that one cause,
it's a little bit of challenge

01:31:54.780 --> 01:31:56.180
to bring people together.

01:31:56.180 --> 01:31:59.250
And we're searching for
that one common cause.

01:31:59.250 --> 01:32:04.010
Maybe struggles against
poverty may be adapted.

01:32:04.010 --> 01:32:12.100
